<Author>Hamstrung
<Content>Comfortable Hotel but a Bit Far from Town... We found this hotel to be quiet, pleasant, and comfortable, though a little far from the centre of town (complicated by the fact that there was train maintenance). Nice river views from our room. Once we sorted out the bus/tram routes - we were fine but next time we would probably stay closer to town as we like to be able to walk to the sights when we are staying for just a few days. Hotel breakfast was not included and, out of character, we decided to try it one morning. It was quite expensive but had an okay selection of food available in the buffet. I would recommend the hotel, but be warned - it is not in the centre of town and not within walking distance to the sights. 
